    "text": "This is the picture of Menachem Begin, myself, and my brother on his visit to Boston in 1973. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The occasion? He was visiting the United States, and he paid a visit to Boston. And since we were youngsters in the old country, belonged to the Betar, we was-- that he was-- they had over in Poland. And he visited our town in Zdolbunow. He knew my dad, and his mentor, Ze'ev Jabotinsky, was-- knew my grandfather. So he felt he wanted to take a picture with us. We were very honored. OK.",
